description: Updates a CloudFront function. You can update a function's code or the comment that describes the function. You cannot update a function's name. To update a function, you provide the function's name and version ( ETag value) along with the updated function code. To get the name and version, you can use ListFunctions and DescribeFunction.

parameters.name: Name
parameters.description: The name of the function that you are updating.

parameters.name: IfMatch
parameters.description: The current version ( ETag value) of the function that you are updating, which you can get using DescribeFunction.

parameters.name: FunctionConfig
parameters.description: Configuration information about the function. A comment to describe the function. The function's runtime environment version. KeyValueStoreAssociations (dict) --- The configuration for the key value store associations. The quantity of key value store associations. Items (list) --- The items of the key value store association. (dict) --- The key value store association. The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the key value store association.

nested_params.name: Comment
nested_params.description: A comment to describe the function.

nested_params.name: KeyValueStoreAssociations
nested_params.description: The configuration for the key value store associations.

nested_params.name: Quantity
nested_params.description: The quantity of key value store associations.

nested_params.name: Items
nested_params.description: The items of the key value store association.

nested_params.name: KeyValueStoreARN
nested_params.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the key value store association.

parameters.name: FunctionCode
parameters.description: The function code. For more information about writing a CloudFront function, see Writing function code for CloudFront Functions in the Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide.
